comments.body:
@ypu thanks for taking a look, and for letting us know about the spring festival.

I chatted with @edsantiago some more on this.  We both still think golang and ginkgo (in general) are not a good fit for what the system-tests need to do.  They're going to gate at the RPM/packaging level, so there is very little, and very slow, feedback when they break.  So simplicity is key, I even wonder if maybe BATS is too much.  Maybe we can just have a simple shell-script.

For this PR, it is only about making a list of what we need.  I will hopefully have that finished before you get back.  Ed said he will work on adding a few starting/basic system-tests in another PR.  So we can get the packaging side of this up and working.  Then we can work to add more system-test later from this 'TODO' list.

@TomSweeneyRedHat @umohnani8 Mind taking a quick peek, to see if there are any glaring typos here?

This is just high-level documentation and a TODO list, no actual code, only my ramblings :smile:
(Ed's PR #2533 backs this PR up with some actual code)

/approve
LGTM
@TomSweeneyRedHat mind giving one more ack so we can merge?
